Detailed Description

cvmx_sli_pkt_cnt_int

This register specifies which output packet rings are interrupting because of packet counters. A bit set in this interrupt register will set a corresponding bit in SLI_PKT_INT and can also cause SLI_MAC()_PF()_INT_SUM[PCNT] to be set if SLI_PKT()_OUTPUT_CONTROL[CENB] is set. When read by a function, this register informs which rings owned by the function (0 to N, N as large as 63) have this interrupt pending.
